It + Be + Noun + Infinite/That

We can use it + be + noun + infinite/that to describe how we feel about a situation.
Common nouns used in this structure are pleasure, shame, pity, thrill, mistake, suprise, and crime.

Infinite
It's a pleasure to meet you.

It was a pity to leave early.

It was real thrill to see him in concert.

It's almost a crime to eat such a beautiful dessert.

It will be a mistake to quit now.


That Clause

It's a pity (that) we have to go now.

It's a shame (that) we didn't have more time.

It was a suprise (that) he didn't tell me he was leaving.

You can use these structures without that.
